The paper deals with a fundamental data structure (graphs) and proposes a new algorithm for a widely used proximity measure (random walk with restart). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a solution for a problem that is relevant to several applications such as recommender systems and link prediction, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of sparse matrices, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm that improves the efficiency of the search for top-k nodes, which could be related to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
